Scatter Matrix by Bokeh Interact¶

def scatter_matrix(col1, col2):
    if col1 == "1st Principal Component":
        index1 = 0
    elif col1 == "2nd Principal Component":
        index1 = 1
    elif col1 == "3rd Principal Component":
        index1 = 2
    elif col1 == "4th Principal Component":
        index1 = 3
    elif col1 == "5th Principal Component":
        index1 = 4
    if col2 == "1st Principal Component":
        index2 = 0
    elif col2 == "2nd Principal Component":
        index2 = 1
    elif col2 == "3rd Principal Component":
        index2 = 2
    elif col2 == "4th Principal Component":
        index2 = 3
    elif col2 == "5th Principal Component":
        index2 = 4
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16,12))
    palette = np.array(seaborn.color_palette("hls", 16))
    rownum, colnum = np.where(y_dummies.values == 1)
    patches = []
    for idx, c in enumerate(palette[np.unique(colnum)]):
        patches.append(mpatches.Patch(color=c, label=y_dummies.columns[idx]))
    plt.scatter(X_pca[:, index1], X_pca[:, index2], c=palette[colnum])
    plt.legend(handles=patches)
    push_notebook()

interact(scatter_matrix, col1=["1st Principal Component", "2nd Principal Component", "3rd Principal Component", 
                              "4th Principal Component", "5th Principal Component"], 
        col2=["1st Principal Component", "2nd Principal Component", "3rd Principal Component", 
                              "4th Principal Component", "5th Principal Component"])

PCA Results on Explained Variance Ratio¶

In [9]:
def min_max_column_pca(dimension):
    components = pca.components_[dimension-1]
    cols = X_dummies.columns
    min_ = np.min(components)
    max_ = np.max(components)
    argmin_ = np.argmin(components)
    argmax_ = np.argmax(components)
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16,2))
    plt.text(0.4, 0.2, "Min Value {min}".format(min=min_))
    plt.text(0.4, 0.4, "Max Value {max}".format(max=max_))
    plt.text(0.4, 0.6, "Min Column {mincol}".format(mincol=cols[argmin_]))
    plt.text(0.4, 0.8, "Max Column {maxcol}".format(maxcol=cols[argmax_]))
    push_notebook()

interact(min_max_column_pca, dimension=[1, 2, 3, 4, 5])

    elif feat_groups1 == "pv3":

        X = pd.concat([X, df.loc[:, ["pv1"]]], axis=1)
    elif feat_groups2 == "pv2":
        X = pd.concat([X, df.loc[:, ["pv2"]]], axis=1)
    elif feat_groups2 == "pv3":

        X = pd.concat([X, df.loc[:, ["pv4"]]], axis=1)
    dummies = pd.get_dummies(X)
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(24,16))

def lag_plot(col):
    data = X_dummies.loc[:, col]
    series = np.cumsum(data)
    series = pd.Series(series)
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12,8))
    pd.plotting.lag_plot(series, lag=1)
    push_notebook()

Distribution plot of PCA transformed space with Best Fit Distribution¶

In [14]:
from scipy.stats import gamma, rayleigh, norm,  nakagami, expon, lognorm, exponweib

# Akaike Information Criterion
def distribution_fitter(component):
    components_ = [
     "1st Principal Component", 
     "2nd Principal Component", 
     "3rd Principal Component", 
     "4th Principal Component", 
     "5th Principal Component"]
    idx = components_.index(component)
    X = df.loc[y.index, ["Month", "HQ", "re1", "re2", "re3", "re4", "bm1", "bm2", "bm3", "bm4", "pv1", "pv2", "pv3", "pv4"]]
    X_dummies = pd.get_dummies(X)
    pca = PCA(n_components=5)
    X_pca = pca.fit_transform(X_dummies)
    n = len(X_pca)
    # gamma distribution
    gammaParam = gamma.fit(X_pca[:, idx])
    gammaNumPar = len(gammaParam)
    gammaSum = -1*np.sum(np.log(gamma.pdf(X_pca[:, idx], *gammaParam)))
    aicGamma = 2*gammaNumPar+2*gammaSum + (2*gammaNumPar*(gammaNumPar+1)
                                           / (n-gammaNumPar-1))

    # rayleigh distribution
    rayleighParam = rayleigh.fit(X_pca[:, idx])
    rayleighNumPar = len(rayleighParam)
    rayleighSum = -1*np.sum(np.log(rayleigh.pdf(X_pca[:, idx],
                                                *rayleighParam)))
    aicRayleigh = 2*rayleighNumPar+2*rayleighSum+(2*rayleighNumPar
                                                  * (rayleighNumPar+1) /
                                                  (n-rayleighNumPar-1))

    # normal distribution
    normParam = norm.fit(X_pca[:, idx])
    normNumPar = len(normParam)
    normSum = -1*np.sum(np.log(norm.pdf(X_pca[:, idx], *normParam)))
    aicNorm = 2*normNumPar+2*normSum+(2*normNumPar*(normNumPar+1)
                                      / (n-normNumPar-1))

    # LogNormal distribution
    logNormParam = lognorm.fit(X_pca)
    logNormNumPar = len(logNormParam)
    logNormSum = -1*np.sum(np.log(lognorm.pdf(X_pca, *logNormParam)))
    aicLogNorm = 2*logNormNumPar+2*logNormSum+(2*logNormNumPar *
                                               (logNormNumPar+1)
                                               / (n-logNormNumPar-1))

    # Nakagami distribution
    nakagamiParam = nakagami.fit(X_pca[:, idx])
    nakagamiNumPar = len(nakagamiParam)
    nakagamiSum = -1*np.sum(np.log(nakagami.pdf(X_pca[:, idx],
                                                *nakagamiParam)))
    aicNakagami = 2*nakagamiNumPar+2*nakagamiSum+(2*nakagamiNumPar *
                                                  (nakagamiNumPar+1)
                                                  / (n-nakagamiNumPar-1))

    # exponential distribution
    exponParam = expon.fit(X_pca[:, idx])
    exponNumPar = len(exponParam)
    exponSum = -1*np.sum(np.log(expon.pdf(X_pca[:, idx], *exponParam)))
    aicExpon = 2*exponNumPar+2*exponSum + (2*exponNumPar *
                                           (exponNumPar+1)
                                           / (n-exponNumPar-1))

    # weibul distribution
    exponweibParam = exponweib.fit(X_pca[:, idx])
    exponweibNumPar = len(exponweibParam)
    exponweibSum = -1*np.sum(np.log(exponweib.pdf(X_pca[:, idx],
                                                  *exponweibParam)))
    aicExpWeib = 2*exponweibNumPar+2*exponweibSum+(2*exponweibNumPar *
                                                   (exponweibNumPar+1)
                                                   / (n-exponweibNumPar-1))
    
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12,8))
    seaborn.displot(X_pca[:, idx], kind='kde')
    plt.text(0.4, 0.9, str(idx+1) + " Principal Component")
    plt.show()
    
    result = {"Gamma": ("AIC: ", aicGamma, "(a,loc,scale)", gammaParam), 
              "Rayleigh": ("AIC: ", aicRayleigh, "(loc,scale)", rayleighParam), 
              "Normal": ("AIC: ", aicNorm, "(loc,scale)", normParam), 
            "LogNorm": ("AIC: ", "(s,loc,scale)", aicLogNorm, "", logNormParam), 
              "Nakagami": (aicNakagami, "(nu,loc,scale)", nakagamiParam),
            "Exponential Weibull": ("AIC: ", aicExpWeib, "(a,c,loc,scale)", exponweibParam)}
    scores = {"Gamma": aicGamma, "Rayleigh": aicRayleigh, "Normal": aicNorm, "LogNorm": aicLogNorm, 
             "Nakagami": aicNakagami, "Exponential Weibull": aicExpWeib}
    scores_list = sorted(scores, key=scores.get)
    return (scores_list[0], result[scores_list[0]])

iface = gr.Interface(fn=distribution_fitter, 
                     inputs=[gr.inputs.Dropdown([
                         "1st Principal Component", 
                         "2nd Principal Component", 
                         "3rd Principal Component", 
                         "4th Principal Component", 
                         "5th Principal Component"])], 
                     outputs=["text"])
iface.launch()

A DEA Problem with Input = HQ and Output = Stage¶

In [28]:
X_dummies = pd.get_dummies(X.loc[:, ["HQ"]])
df_group = pd.concat([X_dummies, y], axis=1).groupby(by=['Stage']).sum()

s = cvx.Variable(df_group.columns.values.shape[0])
p = cvx.Variable(df_group.index.values.shape[0])

service = cvx.matmul(s, np.sum(df_group.values, axis=0))
privilege = cvx.matmul(p, np.sum(df_group.values, axis=1))

dmu_s = np.random.gamma(39.26460571141969, 0.07005105317485194, df_group.columns.values.shape[0])
dmu_p = np.random.normal(10, 0.3, df_group.index.values.shape[0])

# objective function
objective = cvx.Maximize(privilege)

# constraints
constraints = [cvx.matmul(p, dmu_p) - cvx.matmul(s, dmu_s) <= 0, service == 1, s >= 0, p >= 0]

# use cvxpy to solve the objective
problem = cvx.Problem(objective, constraints).solve(verbose=True, solver=cvx.SCS, max_iters=500)
